{"id":671175940,"lang":"swift","time":"3 months, 1 week","timestamp":1648754588,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"49 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/671175940/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Integer to Roman","memory":"14 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    func intToRoman(_ num: Int) -> String {\n        let keys = [1000, 900, 500, 400, 100, 90, 50, 40, 10, 9, 5, 4, 1]\n        let values = [\"M\", \"CM\", \"D\", \"CD\", \"C\", \"XC\", \"L\", \"XL\", \"X\", \"IX\", \"V\", \"IV\", \"I\"]\n        var hashMap: [Int : String] = [:]\n        \n        for index in 0..<keys.count {\n            hashMap[keys[index]] = values[index]\n        }\n        \n        var output = \"\"\n        var mutableNum = num\n        while mutableNum > 0 {\n            for intNumber in keys {\n                let division = mutableNum / intNumber\n                if division > 0 {\n                    for _ in 0..<division {\n                        output += hashMap[intNumber]!\n                        mutableNum -= intNumber\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        \n        return output\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"integer-to-roman"}
